                            <comment id="17812960" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 31 Jan 2024 22:28:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/driftx/cassandra/commit/f7487de8c52248e4031485b3b87790243fc2c8c0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to fix this which merges cleanly, and I don&apos;t think we need CI since we&apos;re already using this option elsewhere in the config.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17812973" author="edimitrova" created="Wed, 31 Jan 2024 22:56:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks good, but we need to use the new template to update the config.yml, config.yml.FREE, config.yml.PAID too. You can do that by running &lt;em&gt;.circleci/generate.sh -a&lt;/em&gt;. Technically, you may also need to update the patch file, but it might not be needed in this case. It must be verified if it applies as expected and with no hook warnings. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17813400" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 1 Feb 2024 20:39:54 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It looks good, but we need to use the new template&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

